      "text": "This document is the Official Gazette of the Government of Maldives, Volume 53, Issue 230, dated 17 Jumada al-Akhirah 1446 AH (corresponding to December 17, 2024).\n\nThe gazette announces **Law Number 33/2024**, which is the **\"Law to bring the 6th Amendment to Law Number 9/2014 (Penal Code of Maldives).\"** [INDEX 1, 3]\n\nThis amendment was passed by the People\u0027s Majlis on December 9, 2024, during its 58th session, and ratified by the President on December 17, 2024. [INDEX 1]\n\nThe key change introduced by this amendment is the addition of **Chapter 240** to Law Number 9/2014. This new chapter introduces several new offenses related to computer and cybercrimes. [INDEX 3]\n\nThe new offenses outlined in Chapter 240 include:\n\n*   **Article 240:** Unauthorized access to computer systems. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 241:** Unauthorized access to computer systems with the intent to commit further offenses. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 242:** Unauthorized interception of computer data. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 243:** Unauthorized interference with data. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 244:** Unauthorized interference with systems. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 245:** Misuse of devices. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 246:** Cyberstalking and acts related to child pornography. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 247:** Computer-related forgery. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 248:** Computer-related fraud. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 249:** Infringement of copyright and related rights. [INDEX 3]\n*   **Article 250:** Definitions of terms used in the chapter. [INDEX 3]\n\nThe document also provides contact information for the President\u0027s Office and the Gazette office, including phone numbers, email (legalaffairs@po.gov.mv), and website (www.gazette.gov.mv). It also mentions the procedure for submitting documents for publication in the gazette. [INDEX 1]",
